MS NID 6

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-Thin', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Serif Myanmar' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Noto Serif Myanmar Thin'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtraLight' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtLt' (NID 1).

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Myanmar ExtBd Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtraBold' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtBd' (NID 1).

Pass
